<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><Section Number="0335.01" xmlns="http://StatRev.xsd"><Catchline xml:space="preserve">Designation and systemization of public roads.</Catchline><SectionBody><Subsection Id="1"><Text xml:space="preserve" Style="Intro">All roads which are open and available for use by the public and dedicated to the public use, according to law or by prescription, are hereby declared to be, and are established as, public roads.</Text></Subsection><Subsection Id="2"><Text xml:space="preserve" Style="Intro">Public roads shall be divided into four systems:</Text><Paragraph Id="a"><Text xml:space="preserve" Style="Intro">The State Highway System;</Text></Paragraph><Paragraph Id="b"><Text xml:space="preserve" Style="Intro">The State Park Road System;</Text></Paragraph><Paragraph Id="c"><Text xml:space="preserve" Style="Intro">The county road system; and</Text></Paragraph><Paragraph Id="d"><Text xml:space="preserve" Style="Intro">The city street system.</Text></Paragraph></Subsection></SectionBody><History xml:space="preserve">s. 25, ch. 29965, 1955; s. 6, ch. 77-165; s. 31, ch. 84-309.</History></Section>